    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-02-16T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-02-16T03:00:00-05:00" n="161"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d161">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/12432: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Canton</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Linnell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-02-16T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 16, 1938—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 16—8:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Foreign flag, chiefly British, Canton bound river steamers including A. P.
                        C.<note n="94" xml:id="d161fn94">Asiatic Petroleum Company (British).</note>
                    oil lighters on first voyage following reopening of river signaled and boarded
                    by two parties from three Japanese destroyers below Bocca Tigris yesterday and
                    warned dangerous to proceed because forts likely to be shelled. China navigation
                    steamer <hi rend="italic">Fatshan</hi> proceeded Canton despite warning without
                    incident reporting a few shells heard but no bombardment. All other vessels
                    returned Hong Kong or Macao. Believed Japanese hoped by action to discourage
                    river traffic.</p>
                <p>Press reports recent courtesy visit to Canton of Eighth Route Army
                    representative.</p>
                <p>Mailed Hong Kong, Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Linnell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
